BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:j6UI3F08cOjgtLQJwgE2e
SUMMARY:Seattle Home & Garden Show\, February 19-22 at Lumen Field Event Ce
	nter
DTSTAMP:20260214T003547Z
DTSTART:20260222T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Now in its 82nd year\, the ‘granddaddy’ of West Coast home and 
	garden consumer shows is presented by SkyDADU and features a big line-up o
	f attractions including celebrity antiques appraiser Dr. Lori\, gardening 
	guru Ciscoe Morris\; the “Shop & Adopt Dog Corral”\; the “Yard to Table” a
	rea with products and services for the garden\, cutting edge 3D printing f
	or the building industry and more than 40 free seminars presented by H&R B
	lock\, to name a few.\n\nHundreds of exhibitors and experts share fresh id
	eas about housing options\, home decor\, design and remodeling\, D.I.Y. re
	sources\, urban farm and garden offerings\, pet-friendly attractions and m
	uch more.\n\n**Attractions:**\n\n·       **Celebrity antiques appraiser Dr
	. Lori** shares her extensive knowledge of potential treasures\, heirlooms
	 and thrift store finds submitted by showgoers. Always informative and ent
	ertaining\, Dr. Lori will host her lively “Antiques Appraisal Comedy Show”
	 at Stage Two on Friday\, Feb. 20 and Saturday\, Feb. 21 at 12:30 p.m. and
	 2:30 p.m.\n\n·       The DADU (Detached Accessory Dwelling Unit) housing 
	segment presents income producing opportunities\, and veteran homebuilder 
	and DADU visionary **Tod Sakai\, CEO of SkyDADU**\, shares the latest info
	rmation in his "DADU Law Decoded – How It Creates New Opportunity**”** sem
	inar presentations each day of the show at 1 p.m.\, located at Stage Two.\
	n\n ·       The show’s **“Yard to Table”** feature spotlights vertical gar
	dening for small spaces\, raised bed gardening\, hydroponic gardening prod
	ucts\, flower and bulb sales and more. **Gardening expert Ciscoe Morris** 
	wows audiences with his encyclopedic knowledge and signature humor on Sund
	ay. Note to dogs and their owners: the show welcomes ticketholders and the
	ir dogs to the show Saturday\, February 21 – at no extra charge!\n\n ·    
	   The **“Shop-and-Adopt Dog Corral”** features dog adoptions from **Jenni
	's Rescue Ranch** and includes more than 20 dogs and puppies available for
	 adoption. The “Corral” includes exhibitors offering pet-related products 
	and services\, including pet “accident” resistant **Pet Decorator®** hardw
	ood floors.\n\n ·       **Versatile “tiny homes” and smaller live/work bui
	ldings** are attracting a growing number of buyers. Featured models on dis
	play come from award-winning **DeTray’s Custom Housing**\, **Mount Baker T
	iny Homes** and **Seattle Tiny Homes.**\n\n·       **The future of 3D prin
	ting in landscaping and construction** **is here** as the Cement Masons an
	d Plasterers Training Centers of Washington highlight the game-changing be
	nefits of this technology for builders\, contractors and architects in a m
	ajor display with a truck-sized boom printer and more.\n\n·       Attendee
	s of all ages are invited to participate in the popular **Emerald City LAN
	Fest**\, building healthy communities through inclusive gaming opportuniti
	es. It features PC gaming\, console gaming and board games for the entire 
	family
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/seattle-home-garden-show-
	february-19-22-at-lumen-field-event-center/17914611/2026-02-22T00
LOCATION:Lumen Field\, 800 Occidental Ave S\,\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT8H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3DhEmkYtkn2mVJXv8xEV0
SUMMARY:Amplify: a hands-on marketing workshop for artists
DTSTAMP:20260214T003547Z
DTSTART:20260222T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Event Types: Arts\,Community\,Education\,Special Events\,Tra in
	ing-Classes/Workshops\,Youth\n\nNeighborhoods: Citywide\,Pioneer Squar e\n
	\nContact: Rana San\n\nContact Phone: \\(206\\) 256-6279\n\nContact Email:
	 rana.san@seattle.gov\n\nAudience: All\n\nPre-Register: No\n\nCost: Free\n
	\nArtists of all disciplines and career stages benefit from building a str
	ong toolkit to promote their work\, apply for funding and residencies\, an
	d pursue press opportunities. In this free two-day intensive \, you'll lea
	rn foundational marketing skills and create resources you can use right aw
	ay.\n\nThrough hands-on activities and e xpert QandAs\, you'll:\n\nDraft o
	r refresh your artist bi o and project description\n\nCreate a clear strat
	egy for digital and social media marketing\n\nLearn to present your work a
	nd organize your materials\n\nGain insights from industry pros\n\nReceive 
	a free professional headshot\n\nMake con nections with fellow Seattle arti
	sts\n\nYou'll walk away with concrete tools\, organized assets\, and renew
	ed confidence to share your work with the world.\n\nSchedule:\n\nFeb. 21 a
	nd 22\n\n10 a.m. - 5 p.m. \\(Lunch break included\\) 0\;\n\nDoors open at 
	9:30 a.m.\n\nAbout the facil itators:\n\nTiffany N. Tomkinson\n\nSeattle P
	hotographer\, Video Producer\, Photojournalist\n\nGro wing up 4th generati
	on in the printing industry and starting my own DIY print zine as a teenag
	er\, Tiffany has been inspired by the power of visual imagery to convey au
	thentic human experience. Today Tiffany works as a professional photograph
	er\, video producer\, and photojournalist in t he greater Seattle area. Ti
	ffany works with musicians\, artists\, and or ganizations to produce photo
	 and video campaigns from creative conception to completion.\n\nTiffany's 
	work has been featured in a number of prominent Northwest outlets\, includ
	ing KEXP\, YES! Magazine \, NPR\, King 5's Evening Magazine\, Seattle Rock
	 Orchestra\, and t he Leukemia and Lymphoma Society.\n\ncenterpointphotogr
	aphy.com\n\n| IG:\n\n@center.point.photography\n\nShaudi Bianca Vahdat\n\n
	Composer\, songwriter\, performer\, and digital and social media marketing
	 special ist\n\nShaudi Bianca Vahdat specializes in digital and s ocial me
	dia marketing for independent artists and organizations. She consults on c
	ontent strategy\, branding\, and campaigns that help artists c onnect with
	 audiences by sharing their work authentically. She is also a freelance wr
	iter for The Wrapbook Blog\, where she covers a range of topics for filmma
	kers.\n\nShaudi is also a musician\, composer and theatre artist. She has 
	performed and/or composed for organizations like Washington Ensemble Theat
	re\, Book-It Repertory Theatre\, The Bushw ick Book Club\, Seattle Arts an
	d Lectures\, and Opera House Arts in S tonington\, Maine. She served as a 
	Fall 2024 Artist-in-Residence at Inscape Arts\, and presented her original
	 musical The Golden Door: an American immigrant song cycle in 2025 at Seat
	tle Center as part of the Artists at the Center program as well as an enco
	re co-production with Seattle Open Arts Place. She is also a current advis
	or for the City of Seattle's ARTS at King Street Station program.\n\nShaud
	i holds a Master of Music in Contemporary Performance from Berklee College
	 of Music and a B.A. in Drama Performance from the University of Washingto
	n Seattle.\n\nshaudibiancavahdat.com\n\n| IG:\n\n@shaudibianca\n\nAbout th
	e series:\n\nThe\n\ncommUNITY series\n\nis a selection of free public prog
	rams that center connection\, career development\, and the co-creation of 
	art. Curated by\n\nARTS at King Street Station Advisors \, this series bri
	ngs together their visions and talents to build community\, engage attende
	es in powerful arts practices\, and offer free career development and skil
	l-building for all ages. This series features workshops by Ashanti Davis\,
	 Alicia Mullikin\, Shaudi Vahdat\, Scott Oshima\, and Marie Kidhe.
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/amplify-a-hands-on-market
	ing-workshop-for-artists/17661051/2026-02-22T00
LOCATION:ARTS at King Street Station\, 303 S. Jackson Street\, Top Floo r\,
	 Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
